subject: p19800337
History: Year old woman with high fever and cough for 5 days, hypoxemia, r/o pneumonia.
Findings: Multifocal patchy opacities in the right middle, right upper, and bilateral lower lobes are concerning for pneumonia. The most severe consolidation is in the right middle lobe. The lungs are without pleural effusion or pneumothorax. The cardiac and mediastinal contours are normal.
Impression: Multifocal pneumonia most severe in the right middle lobe.
